</div>Helpful or harmful to whom indeed; that&#8217;s always the question with politics.  Anyhow, my thought too was that the Government would use its leverage in order to make more loans, and increased access to capital is obviously  a necessary component of ending the recession.  My concern is both that the government may minimize loan risk, which is after all how this crisis came about, and that the banks &#8220;hoarding money&#8221; may be a rational decision &#8211; we suspect many banks may already be insolvent.  <br />
<br />
I just hope that the Government considers the banks&#8217; fiscal position when formulating credit policy, or else the banks are just going to be monetary spigots, spewing out money from the treasury.  At this point, maybe I shouldn&#8217;t care; it&#8217;s fairly obvious how the Government will eventually eliminate the deficits and the national debt, so what&#8217;s a little more play money?</div>
