Nationalization is probably the most free-market-ish thing we can do right now (short of letting everything just crash, which no one wants to do). But Americans have this stupid idea that nationalization = socialism when nationalization is just an action, and socialism is motivation. So instead we do what the American people think of as not-socialism (keep the government from owning the banks while not letting them crash), but in reality it is pure corporate socialism.</div>
